page.title: 19WILDLIFE
page.content: {BIRDS.}THERE ARE MANY BIRDS INCLUDING BUZZARDS,CROWS,MAGPIE,JAYS,ROOKS, KESTRELS,SPAROWHAWKS,BARN AND TAWNY OWLS,HERONS,KINFISHERS,DIPPERS,MALLARD S,PHEASANTS,LAPWINGS,WAGTAILS,GREEN,GR EATER,SPOTTED AND LESSER SPOTTED WOODPECKERS,TREE CREEPERS,NUTHATCH, FIELDFARE AND REDWING AND MANY SMALL COMMON BIRDS.{INSECTS.}LARGE NUMBERS OF INSECTS AT LEAST 15 VARIETYS OF BUTTERFLIES MANY BEETLES AND SPIDERS. {CONSERVATION.}THE FARMERS ARE ENCOURAGED TO CONSERVE AREAS OF WOODLANDS,HEDGES AND OTHER WILDLIFE HABITATS.SOME WILDLIFE HAS TO BE CONTROLLED DEER ARE CULLED FOXES ARE HUNTED.THERE ARE MANY FOOTPATHES THROUGH FIELDS AND WOODS.{POLLUTION. } THE VARIETY OF LICHENS ON OUR TREES SHOW THE LOW LEVEL POLLUTION HERE. SOME STREAMS ARE POLLUTED BY FARM WASTE AND CHEMICALS.
